The set of living organisms that live in a certain environment and form a single whole with it is called an ecosystem. So, the correct answer is d) ecosystem.
A marine ecosystem is c) estuary.
A freshwater ecosystem is d) reef (although a freshwater ecosystem can also be a swamp or an estuary).
A terrestrial ecosystem is a) reef, but in this context it should be d) tundra, taiga, swamp, or any other terrestrial biome.
The layer of a broadleaf forest to which old oak trees belong is the third layer (d) fourth if we count from the bottom up).
In the forest ecosystem, the producer is d) trees (specifically linden in this case).
The autumn honeysuckle, which parasitizes on pine trees, is a reducer (b).
The oyster mushroom common, which destroys the wood of dead poplar trees, is a decomposer (c) first-order consumer as it feeds on dead organic matter, but in this context it's a decomposer.
An abiotic factor for a mouse living in a broad-leaved forest is d) air temperature.
An example of predation is the interaction between a mouse and an owl (c).
An example of mutualism is the interaction between ants and aphids (d).
An example of competition is the interaction between two mice of the same species (b).
